snippets.title: CompletionService completeQuery Sample
snippets.description: Completes the specified user input with keyword suggestions.

snippets.title: CompletionService purgeSuggestionDenyListEntries Sample
snippets.description: Permanently deletes all [SuggestionDenyListEntry][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.SuggestionDenyListEntry] for a DataStore.

snippets.title: CompletionService purgeCompletionSuggestions Sample
snippets.description: Permanently deletes all [CompletionSuggestion][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.CompletionSuggestion]s for a DataStore.

snippets.title: CompletionService createControl Sample
snippets.description: Creates a Control. By default 1000 controls are allowed for a data store. A request can be submitted to adjust this limit. If the [Control][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Control] to create already exists, an ALREADY_EXISTS error is returned.

snippets.title: CompletionService deleteControl Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a Control. If the [Control][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Control] to delete does not exist, a NOT_FOUND error is returned.

snippets.title: CompletionService updateControl Sample
snippets.description: Updates a Control. [Control][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Control] action type cannot be changed. If the [Control][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Control] to update does not exist, a NOT_FOUND error is returned.

snippets.title: CompletionService listControls Sample
snippets.description: Lists all Controls by their parent [DataStore][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.DataStore].

snippets.title: CompletionService createConversation Sample
snippets.description: Creates a Conversation. If the [Conversation][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Conversation] to create already exists, an ALREADY_EXISTS error is returned.

snippets.title: CompletionService deleteConversation Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a Conversation. If the [Conversation][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Conversation] to delete does not exist, a NOT_FOUND error is returned.

snippets.title: CompletionService updateConversation Sample
snippets.description: Updates a Conversation. [Conversation][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Conversation] action type cannot be changed. If the [Conversation][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Conversation] to update does not exist, a NOT_FOUND error is returned.

snippets.title: CompletionService listConversations Sample
snippets.description: Lists all Conversations by their parent [DataStore][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.DataStore].

snippets.title: CompletionService createSession Sample
snippets.description: Creates a Session. If the [Session][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Session] to create already exists, an ALREADY_EXISTS error is returned.

snippets.title: CompletionService deleteSession Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a Session. If the [Session][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Session] to delete does not exist, a NOT_FOUND error is returned.

snippets.title: CompletionService updateSession Sample
snippets.description: Updates a Session. [Session][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Session] action type cannot be changed. If the [Session][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Session] to update does not exist, a NOT_FOUND error is returned.

snippets.title: CompletionService listSessions Sample
snippets.description: Lists all Sessions by their parent [DataStore][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.DataStore].

snippets.title: CompletionService createDataStore Sample
snippets.description: Creates a [DataStore][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.DataStore]. DataStore is for storing [Documents][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Document]. To serve these documents for Search, or Recommendation use case, an [Engine][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Engine] needs to be created separately.

snippets.title: CompletionService listDataStores Sample
snippets.description: Lists all the [DataStore][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.DataStore]s associated with the project.

snippets.title: CompletionService importDocuments Sample
snippets.description: Bulk import of multiple [Document][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Document]s. Request processing may be synchronous. Non-existing items are created. Note: It is possible for a subset of the [Document][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Document]s to be successfully updated.

snippets.title: CompletionService purgeDocuments Sample
snippets.description: Permanently deletes all selected [Document][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Document]s in a branch. This process is asynchronous. Depending on the number of [Document][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Document]s to be deleted, this operation can take hours to complete. Before the delete operation completes, some [Document][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Document]s might still be returned by [DocumentService.GetDocument][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.DocumentService.GetDocument] or [DocumentService.ListDocuments][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.DocumentService.ListDocuments]. To get a list of the [Document][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Document]s to be deleted, set [PurgeDocumentsRequest.force][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.PurgeDocumentsRequest.force] to false.

snippets.title: CompletionService batchGetDocumentsMetadata Sample
snippets.description: Gets index freshness metadata for [Document][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Document]s. Supported for website search only.

snippets.title: CompletionService listEngines Sample
snippets.description: Lists all the [Engine][google.cloud.discoveryengine.v1.Engine]s associated with the project.

snippets.title: CompletionService provisionProject Sample
snippets.description: Provisions the project resource. During the process, related systems will get prepared and initialized. Caller must read the [Terms for data use](https://cloud.google.com/retail/data-use-terms), and optionally specify in request to provide consent to that service terms.

snippets.title: CompletionService rank Sample
snippets.description: Ranks a list of text records based on the given input query.

snippets.title: CompletionService recommend Sample
snippets.description: Makes a recommendation, which requires a contextual user event.

snippets.title: CompletionService listCustomModels Sample
snippets.description: Gets a list of all the custom models.

snippets.title: CompletionService enableAdvancedSiteSearch Sample
snippets.description: Upgrade from basic site search to advanced site search.

snippets.title: CompletionService disableAdvancedSiteSearch Sample
snippets.description: Downgrade from advanced site search to basic site search.

snippets.title: CompletionService recrawlUris Sample
snippets.description: Request on-demand recrawl for a list of URIs.

snippets.title: CompletionService batchVerifyTargetSites Sample
snippets.description: Verify target sites' ownership and validity. This API sends all the target sites under site search engine for verification.

snippets.title: CompletionService fetchDomainVerificationStatus Sample
snippets.description: Returns list of target sites with its domain verification status. This method can only be called under data store with BASIC_SITE_SEARCH state at the moment.

snippets.title: CompletionService collectUserEvent Sample
snippets.description: Writes a single user event from the browser. This uses a GET request to due to browser restriction of POST-ing to a third-party domain. This method is used only by the Discovery Engine API JavaScript pixel and Google Tag Manager. Users should not call this method directly.

snippets.title: CompletionService purgeUserEvents Sample
snippets.description: Deletes permanently all user events specified by the filter provided. Depending on the number of events specified by the filter, this operation could take hours or days to complete. To test a filter, use the list command first.

snippets.title: CompletionService importUserEvents Sample
snippets.description: Bulk import of user events. Request processing might be synchronous. Events that already exist are skipped. Use this method for backfilling historical user events. Operation.response is of type ImportResponse. Note that it is possible for a subset of the items to be successfully inserted. Operation.metadata is of type ImportMetadata.
